article.description: Kris Dunn scored a career-high 32 points and Rodney Bullock added 20 -- also a career best -- as Providence defeated Harvard 76-64 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Providence tops Harvard 76-64 behind Dunn's career night
article.linkText: Providence tops Harvard 76-64 behind Dunn's career night
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Kris Dunn scored a career-high 32 points and Rodney Bullock added 20 -- also a career best -- as Providence defeated Harvard 76-64 on Saturday night. Dunn sank 11 of 26 shots and was 9 of 11 from the foul line as the Friars (1-0) held off Harvard. Freshman Corey Johnson led the Crimson (1-1) with 17 points -- including five 3-pointers. Harvard was 9 of 20 from 3-point range, the most since making 12 against Penn in 2014. Providence was 18 of 21 from the foul line, while Harvard was 7 of 13. Dunn also had five assists and grabbed eight steals while the entire Crimson squad made three. Zena Edosomwan scored 13 points with 16 rebounds for Harvard, his first double-double. An Edosomwan dunk tied the game at 41-41, but Bullock sparked an 18-5 run for Providence with a layup, and Dunn capped the run with a 3-pointer, as the Friars pulled away.
